'''Sarius Guile''' is a servant of [[Vanescula Drakan]] and is first seen during the [[Darkness of Hallowvale]] quest. She lives in a house on the east side of [[Meiyerditch]], although she is never home. Instead, she is likely in or around [[Castle Drakan]], working. She is humbly dressed, but her status as servant of a Drakan still makes her exude something of importance, unlike the frail [[Meiyerditch citizen]]s. She is still extremely lean, however, which may mean Sarius has to pay [[blood tithe]]s as well.

During [[Darkness of Hallowvale]], she saves the player from their death at the hands of [[Vanstrom Klause]], under the orders of [[Vanescula Drakan]]. With Vanstrom gone, she gives the player a hint about a hidden letter in [[Mauritys Guile|her father]]'s former house. The player discovers that Vanescula has an interest in [[Safalaan]], the [[Myreque]] leader of the [[Sanguinesti region]].

During [[Sins of the Father]], Sarius comes to the player's aid once again. She had been tasked by Vanescula with keeping a distant eye on the player while they were in Darkmeyer. Just as Vanstrom is about to discover the player's identity in the prison, Sarius appears and diverts his attention.

